[SN]TITLE[SN]
Sheepdog rescued after mine fall near Lake Vyrnwy

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A dog had a lucky escape after falling down an old mine near Lake Vyrnwy in Powys on Sunday.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The sheepdog had become trapped near the village of Penybontfawr at about 12:30 BST.
A fire crew from Llanfair was involved in the rescue, along with search and rescue and cave rescue teams.
The dog was raised with a special harness before being reunited with his owner hours later.
